Clemens Boersig, chairman of the
supervisory board of Deutsche Bank AG, said he will decide who
succeeds  Josef Ackermann , management-board chairman,  Frankfurter
Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung  reported.  Boersig told the newspaper that the supervisory board, and
primarily its chairman, makes the decision. Ackermann was quoted
by the paper as saying that he shows no personal preferences as
to who gets the job.  To contact the reporter on this story:
